1 1. Increasing the number of skilled construction workers in this State;
2 2. Ensuring the highest quality of work on such projects;
3 3. Ensuring the safe and timely completion of such projects; [and]
4 4. Ensuring that the residents of this State have access to safe, reliable and
5 affordable energy resources [.] ; and
6 5. Enhancing public safety.
7 Sec. 3. 1. Except as otherwise provided in subsection 2, the provisions of
8 NRS 338.013 to 338.090, inclusive, apply to any contract for construction work
9 awarded by a public utility to a contractor or subcontractor on a significant
10 operational or capital requirement project [, even if] when the construction work
11 does not qualify as a public work [,] as defined in NRS 338.010.
12 2. The provisions of subsection 1 do not apply to a contract awarded by a
13 public utility where the primary construction work will be performed by a
14 contractor with:
15 (a) A collective bargaining agreement;
16 (b) A project labor agreement; or
17 (c) A worksite agreement that provides for the construction of a significant
18 operational or capital requirement project, or for the maintenance of, or other
19 [going] ongoing work to be performed upon completion of, a significant
20 operational or capital requirement project.
21 3. As used in this section:
22 (a) “Public utility” means a utility that purchases natural gas for retail . [and
23 an electric utility as defined in NRS 704.7571.]
24 (b) “Significant operational or capital requirement project” means [:
25 (1) The construction or] the replacement of a natural gas pipeline
26 approved in a plan submitted pursuant to NRS 704.991 . [; or
27 (2) The construction of a new generation electric utility facility of not
28 less than 50 megawatts and that is approved in a plan submitted pursuant to NRS
29 704.741.]
30 Sec. 4. The provisions of section 3 of this act do not apply to any contract
31 entered into before October 1, 2025.

